#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/how-it-works/date-time.xml:13
msgid ""
"Date and time are represented by an object of <literal>Kernel::System::"
"DateTime</literal>.  Every DateTime object holds its own date, time and time "
"zone information.  In contrast to the now deprecated <literal>Kernel::"
"System::Time</literal> package, this means that you can and should create a "
"DateTime object for every date/time you want to use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/how-it-works/date-time.xml:20
